The main document to author is MDD.dtd, that defines the external subset of the
MDD.xml DTD.

The MDD.dtd document contains comments whose contents is itself XML. The element
names for this documentation XML are themselves derived from the TexInfo markup
tags. Indeed, I wanted to use XML for documentation, but HTML tags do not have
enough structure for such documentation.

The dtd2latex.pl Perl script converts MDD.dtd to MDD.tex, which is then \input
by Design.tex. The formatted documentation is obtained by entering the command:

  make doc

This produces the Design.ps document.

-- Benoit Dupont de Dinechin

